Bring a large #pot{} of salted @water{} to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and slice @button mushrooms{4%ounce}(trimmed and sliced). Trim and thinly
slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced), separating whites from greens.

Once water is boiling, add @penne pasta{6%ounce} to pot. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}.

Reserve 1/2 cup pasta cooking water, then drain.

While pasta cooks, open package of @diced skinless dark meat chicken{10%ounce}
and drain off any excess liquid.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat.
Add chicken, mushrooms, and scallion whites; season with @garlic powder{1%tsp},
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until mushrooms are
browned and tender and chicken is cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in drained penne, 1/4 cup reserved pasta cooking water, @veggie stock
concentrate{1}, @mushroom stock concentrate{1}, @Dijon mustard{2%tsp},
@crème fraîche{2%tbsp}, @butter{2%tbsp}, and a @sugar{pinch}. Cook, stirring,
until sauce is smooth and everything is coated, ~{1-2%minutes}. Taste and
season with salt and pepper if desired.

Divide pasta between shallow bowls. Garnish with scallion greens and serve.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.